<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#871f78">Originally posted by MarkUCLA on 08-18-2001 03:41 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Muse,

I recommend you take the responses that you've received from this post & let Verant know that without your website, many people would have gotten frustrated and not played EQ. I myself had purchased the game & then quit, till I found this & other websites which peeked my interest & I gave it another shot. Many RPG's include built-in maps already so it is not a spoiler, but a necessary guide to enjoy the game better.

In actuality, you've saved us countless hours of exploration so we could spend that time on other quality aspects of the game. Let me give an example of what a true spoiler is. I bought a game, went to a website & went through the Walk-thru. I completed the game in 1 week. It was fun, it was quick. I never got any depth out of it, and Ive never played it again. The countless hours the programmers/developers spent on the work was wasted through the spoiler. I didnt really enjoy the experience very much.

Now, when was the last time someone in EQ played the game, used your website (or any EQ website) as a spoiler, then quit the game because they finished it too soon, or didnt get any depth or enjoyment out of it. The game is not designed that way. It just made me want to do more exploring to those areas I never knew existed. I've been in West Commons for months & never knew Befallen was there. Had it not been for the maps, I would have never found it, or cared.

I will be happy to donate to your site when you set that function up. Thanks for giving me the inspiration to enjoy the game. "After" LUCLIN comes out, and you've mapped everything there (=P), then please enjoy all aspects of RL & good luck in all future endeavors.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
